<includeonly>{| class="wikitable source-semanticschemas"
{{Category/display-header | category={{{category|}}} }}
{{Category/display-rows | category={{{category|}}} | page={{{page|{{FULLPAGENAME}}}}} }}
{{#ifeq:{{{nested|no}}}|no|{{Category/render-reverse | {{{category|}}} }}|}}
|}{{#ifeq:{{{nested|no}}}|no|
{{Category/subobjects | category={{{category|}}} | page={{{page|{{FULLPAGENAME}}}}} }}|}}</includeonly><noinclude>
Dynamic table display template for SemanticSchemas categories.

Composes display-header, display-rows, render-reverse, and subobjects
into a full-width wikitable layout.

Parameters:
* category - The category name (without namespace prefix)
* page - Target page to read property values from. Defaults to
         {{FULLPAGENAME}}; Category/subobject-instance passes a
         subobject fragment here so the same template renders
         individual subobject instances.
* nested - Set to "yes" when Category/table is being re-entered to
         render a subobject instance (the "mini-table" inside an
         enclosing Category/table render). In that mode the Backlinks
         (render-reverse) and subobject sections are suppressed because
         (a) {{FULLPAGENAME}} still points at the parent page, so
         backlinks would duplicate per instance, and (b) we want to
         stop the subobject-section recursion at depth 1. Defaults to
         "no" (top-level render — emit full chrome).
</noinclude>
